# Lighthouse Macro Brand Guide

## Brand Identity

**Company:** Lighthouse Macro
**Tagline:** MACRO, ILLUMINATED.
**Positioning:** Institutional-grade macro and economic intelligence for two audiences — **market participants** (hedge funds, CIOs, central banks, allocators, individual investors) and **non-market participants** (business owners, operators, corporates, policy folks). Canonical articulation: Two Economies / "Most Americans" Beacon, Apr 20 2026.

## Color Palette

### Signature Palette (23/89/BB Mnemonic)

The signature mnemonic is 23/89/BB. Every color contains some combination of 23, 89, and BB — except the surface/contrast utilities (Deep, Ice, Glacier, Foam), which extend the system without breaking it.

**Palette locked 2026-06-16.** Sky is now `#89CCFF` (the old `#23BBFF` and the separate "Bright" are retired — `#89CCFF` reads as a clear lighter companion to Ocean rather than a competing same-hue blue). Deep `#123456` carries dark canvas, wordmark, headings, and the old "Navy" black-replacement in one token. Ice `#D4E2EF` is the visible section-differentiation tint (Glacier was too close to white). Cycle order on white bg: Ocean → Dusk → Sky → Sea → Venus → Doldrums. On dark bg (Deep canvas), Sky is the primary plotting color because Ocean dims against Deep.

| Layer | Name | Hex | Mnemonic | Usage |
|-------|------|-----|----------|-------|
| Primary | Ocean | `#2389BB` | 23+89+BB | Anchor: headers, borders, links, chart primary on white |
| Secondary | Dusk | `#FF6723` | 23 | Antagonist overlay, key insights, CTA buttons, accent bar |
| Secondary | Sky | `#89CCFF` | 89 | 3rd plotting line; promoted to primary on dark theme |
| Dark / ink | Deep | `#123456` | — | Dark canvas, wordmark, headings, high-contrast line on white (replaces black + the old Navy) |
| Tertiary | Sea | `#00BB89` | BB+89 | On-target / win bands, positive 4th line |
| Alert | Venus | `#FF2389` | 23+89 | Critical alerts, 2% target lines |
| Bullish | Starboard | `#238923` | 23+89 | Bullish regime ONLY — pair with a lightness/label cue (red-green colorblind safety) |
| Bearish | Port | `#892323` | 89+23 | Bearish regime ONLY — pair with a lightness/label cue (red-green colorblind safety) |
| Structural | Doldrums | `#898989` | 89+89 | Axis spines, labels, secondary text |

### Surface and Reference Colors

| Name | Hex | Usage |
|------|-----|-------|
| Foam | `#FFFFFF` | Pure white; institutional chart background |
| Glacier | `#F4F7F9` | Barely-there cool off-white; cards, table fills, subtle legend fills |
| Ice | `#D4E2EF` | Visible section-differentiation tint (bluer/darker than Glacier) |
| Fog | `#D1D1D1` | Zero lines, ghost reference lines |

### Chart Background

| Context | Color | Hex |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Primary (all publications) | Foam | `#FFFFFF` |
| Dark variant | Deep | `#123456` |

White theme is primary for Substack, PDF, social, and Chartbook output. Dark theme uses Deep `#123456` as the canvas with Foam/Glacier text/spines and Sky as the primary plotting color.

